main event: A witness observed three objects resembling stars that traveled slowly and silently in the sky on June 6, 1963.
interesting points: The objects were moving slowly and gaining altitude., The sighting lasted for about 10 minutes., The objects made no sound at all., The conclusion drawn was insufficient information with a possibility that the objects were astronomical., The report categorizes the sighting as a civilian observation.
sighted object: three star-like objects in the sky
witness description: The witness was inside a car looking out the window when the sighting occurred.
